-- India's Shriram Transport Fin to raise at least 5 bln rupees via NCDs - sources
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi and Neha Dasgupta
-- Thu Jun 26, 2014 08:32AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 26 (Reuters) - India's Shriram Transport Finance Company Ltd <SRTR.NS> will raise at least 5 billion rupees ($83.75 million) via non-convertible debentures in the first week of July, multiple sources said on Thursday.

The company will raise up to a maximum of 30 billion rupees in 3-, 5- and 7-year tenures, sources said. Edelweiss Capital, ICICI Securities, A.K. Capital and J.M. Financial are among the lead managers of the issue, sources added.